<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-08T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/10–849:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the
                                        Netherlands</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d355fn1">Repeated in telegram Gadel 48,
                                    October 11, 2 p. m., to New York (<gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>).</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-08T18:00:00-05:00">October 8, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>870. <gloss target="#t_Ushic1">Ushic</gloss> 25. <gloss target="#t_Hicus1">Hicus</gloss> 52 and 53.<note n="2" xml:id="d355fn2">Telegram 907 and 908, October 8, <ref target="#pg_503">pp. 503</ref>, <ref target="#pg_505">505</ref>.</note> Neth Amb called Oct 8 his request express
                                his govt’s deep concern developments resulting from your <pb facs="0526" n="512" xml:id="pg_512"/> effort resolve impasse
                                ec-financial negots emphasizing possibility resignation present
                                Cabinet and breakdown <gloss target="#t_RTC1">RTC</gloss>
                                    DepUnderSec.<note n="3" xml:id="d355fn3">Dean Rusk.</note>
                                emphasized purely personal character your proposal, fact that such
                                technique had been used successfully before and expressed hope that
                                Tues meeting would resolve present tension. DepUnderSec added he did
                                not believe Neth Govt justified in making such heayy weather of
                                incident.</p>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Hicus1">Hicus</gloss> 54<note n="4" xml:id="d355fn4">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> received after Amb
                                departed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>